title.narrative: By 2019, capacities of keychild protection service providers -medical, psychosocial and legal, including CSOs - are strengthened to provide quality and coordinated services to at-risk and child victims, including in emergencysituations.

description.narrative: Child protection and health services at central and decentralized levels were strengthened, enabling them to prevent and respond to violence against children and harmful practices (FGM and child marriage) and increasing birth registration. A total of 1,920 children were cared for in 2019 compared with 999 in 2018, Child protection systems at community, institutional and national level are being improved through capacity-building (training, vehicle/motorcycle provision, office equipment and supplies). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
